author: Sinead Maclaughlin For Daily Mail Australia
title: Welcome to Flochella - the music festival that floats | Daily Mail Online
text: Bikinis and bombs at NZ floating music festival Flochella as thousands gather for fun in the sun Thousands dusted off their bikinis for floating music festival Flochella The two-day event at Great Lake Taupo was the first of its kind Around 4000 revellers listened to Kiwi artists like Theia and Jupiter Project The free event also played host to the NZ's Official Bomb Comp Thrill-seekers leapt off 10m scaffold into the water below to impress the judges Published: 03:20 GMT, 6 February 2017 | Updated: 09:31 GMT, 6 February 2017 336 shares
